8. A fuel cell comprising:
a membrane-electrode assembly including a hydrogen ion conductive polymer electrolyte membrane;
a pair of catalyst layers sandwiching said polymer electrolyte membrane;
and a pair of gas diffusion layers disposed on the outer surfaces of said catalyst layers;
the gas diffusion layers having electron conductivity and gas diffusibility, the gas diffusion layers each having a first major surface and a second major surface which is positioned opposite to said first major surface and an interior between said first and second major surfaces;
wherein said gas diffusion layers comprise a porous carbon substrate which is directly fluorinated in said interior and is substantially free of fluorination on at least one of said first major surface or said second major surface.

15. A method for making a gas diffusion device comprising:
providing a porous carbon substrate having a first major surface and a second major surface which is positioned opposite to said first major surface and an interior between said first and second major surfaces;
protecting at least one of the first major surface and second major surface by contacting at the least one surface with a protective layer;
directly fluorinating the porous carbon substrate with fluorine gas;
removing said contact between said protective layer and said at least one surface;
wherein said interior of said gas diffusion device is fluorinated and said at least one surface is not substantially fluorinated.

22. A method for making a gas diffusion device comprising:
providing a porous carbon substrate having a first major surface and a second major surface which is positioned opposite to said first major surface and an interior between said first and second major surfaces; wherein the porous substrate is comprised carbon fibers having thousands of carbon atomic layers;
directly fluorinating the porous carbon substrate with fluorine gas such that an outer carbon atomic layer of said fibers is fluorinated;
removing said outer carbon atomic layers of the carbon fibers forming at least one of said first and second major surfaces such that the interior of said gas diffusion device is fluorinated and at least one major surface is not substantially fluorinated.
